cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.DC, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with localization in a network of mobile robots. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper abstracts the localization algorithm as a Linear Time-Varying (LTV) system. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is another possible category as the paper deals with a network of robots and provides a distributed algorithm for localization. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also possible as the paper provides a distributed algorithm for localization. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with a network of robots and their communication with each other.
